    {
      "id": "sybil_1_listing_1",
      "firm_id": "sybil_1",
      "description": "Hey there! I\u2019m parting ways with my trusty ride, and honestly, it\u2019s been such a joy to drive. It\u2019s in really solid shape\u2014well-maintained, clean, and still has so many adventures left in it! Whether you're ziping through your daily commute or heading out for a weekend getaway, it\u2019s super dependable and runs like a dream. It\u2019s got a few minor signs of love here and there, but it\u2019s a fantastic, reliable car that's ready to hit the road with a new owner. Come take it for a spin and see for yourself!",
      "price": 33500.0,
      "reputation": 0.5,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 24
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available for the discerning driver is this 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six, delivering linear power through six individual throttle bodies and a high-compression valvetrain. This example is paired with the desirable Getrag 420G 6-speed manual transmission and a factory M Variable limited-slip differential. The chassis remains taut, benefiting from a reinforced rear subframe and refreshed polyurethane bushings to mitigate common floor-pan fatigue. The double VANOS system has been professionally serviced to ensure optimal cam timing and peak torque delivery. Finished in a classic colorway, this M3 maintains its original suspension geometry and mechanical integrity, offering the pure analog feedback and 8,000 RPM redline enthusiasts demand. Recent maintenance includes a comprehensive valve adjustment and Inspection II service, ensuring the high-revving internals remain within factory tolerances. A mechanically sound specimen ready for spirited B-road duty.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 24
    },
    {
